{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":136,"text":"I've got a great idea\nthat's going to change the world."},{"time":2780,"text":"It's fantastic, it's going\nto blow your mind."},{"time":5198,"text":"It's my beautiful baby."},{"time":6623,"text":"Here's the thing:\neverybody loves a beautiful baby."},{"time":9076,"text":"I mean, I was a beautiful baby."},{"time":11041,"text":"Here's me and my dad\na couple days after I was born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13541,"text":"So in the world of product design,"},{"time":15204,"text":"the beautiful baby's like the concept car."},{"time":17596,"text":"It's the knockout."},{"time":19506,"text":"You see it and you go, \"Oh, my God.\nI'd buy that in a second!\""},{"time":22669,"text":"So why is it that this year's new cars"},{"time":25064,"text":"look pretty much exactly\nlike last year's new cars?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":28352,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30148,"text":"What went wrong between\nthe design studio and the factory?"},{"time":32990,"text":"Today, I don't want to talk\nabout beautiful babies,"},{"time":35418,"text":"I want to talk about the awkward\nadolescence of design --"},{"time":38183,"text":"those sort of dorky teenage years"},{"time":42785,"text":"where you're trying to figure out\nhow the world works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46307,"text":"I'm going to start with an example"},{"time":47966,"text":"from some work that we did\non newborn health."},{"time":50418,"text":"So here's a problem:"},{"time":52074,"text":"four million babies around the world,\nmostly in developing countries,"},{"time":56113,"text":"die every year\nbefore their first birthday,"},{"time":58498,"text":"even before their first month of life."},{"time":60350,"text":"It turns out half of those kids,"},{"time":62034,"text":"or about 1.8 million newborns\naround the world,"},{"time":64272,"text":"would make it if you could\njust keep them warm"},{"time":67184,"text":"for the first three days,\nmaybe the first week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69930,"text":"So this is a newborn intensive care unit\nin Kathmandu, Nepal."},{"time":73655,"text":"All of these kids in blankets\nbelong in incubators --"},{"time":76388,"text":"something like this."},{"time":78061,"text":"This is a donated Japanese Atom incubator"},{"time":80881,"text":"that we found in a NICU in Kathmandu."},{"time":84125,"text":"This is what we want."},{"time":85315,"text":"Probably what happened is a hospital\nin Japan upgraded their equipment"},{"time":88673,"text":"and donated their old stuff to Nepal."},{"time":92126,"text":"The problem is, without technicians,\nwithout spare parts,"},{"time":95215,"text":"donations like this\nvery quickly turn into junk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99253,"text":"So this seemed like a problem\nthat we could do something about."},{"time":102958,"text":"Keeping a baby warm for a week --\nthat's not rocket science."},{"time":106756,"text":"So we got started."},{"time":108163,"text":"We partnered with a leading medical\nresearch institution here in Boston."},{"time":112058,"text":"We conducted months\nof user research overseas,"},{"time":114998,"text":"trying to think like designers,\nhuman-centered design --"},{"time":117728,"text":"\"Let's figure out what people want.\""},{"time":120575,"text":"We killed thousands of Post-it notes."},{"time":122692,"text":"We made dozens of prototypes\nto get to this."},{"time":126139,"text":"So this is the NeoNurture\ninfant incubator,"},{"time":129131,"text":"and this has a lot of smarts\nbuilt into it, and we felt great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132829,"text":"So the idea here is,\nunlike the concept car,"},{"time":135167,"text":"we want to marry something beautiful"},{"time":137045,"text":"with something that actually works."},{"time":139548,"text":"And our idea is that this design"},{"time":141659,"text":"would inspire manufacturers\nand other people of influence"},{"time":145146,"text":"to take this model and run with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148516,"text":"Here's the bad news:"},{"time":151197,"text":"the only baby ever actually put\ninside the NeoNurture incubator"},{"time":155195,"text":"was this kid during a Time\nmagazine photo shoot."},{"time":159068,"text":"So recognition is fantastic."},{"time":161295,"text":"We want design to get out\nfor people to see it."},{"time":163994,"text":"It won lots of awards."},{"time":165884,"text":"But it felt like a booby prize."},{"time":168906,"text":"We wanted to make beautiful things"},{"time":170630,"text":"that are going to make\nthe world a better place,"},{"time":173791,"text":"and I don't think this kid was even\nin it long enough to get warm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177469,"text":"So it turns out that design \nfor inspiration doesn't really ..."},{"time":183200,"text":"I guess what I would say is,\nfor us, for what I want to do,"},{"time":186750,"text":"it's either too slow or it just\ndoesn't work, it's ineffective."},{"time":190184,"text":"So, really, I want to design for outcomes."},{"time":193245,"text":"I don't want to make beautiful stuff;\nI want to make the world a better place."},{"time":196965,"text":"So when we were designing NeoNurture,"},{"time":198774,"text":"we paid a lot of attention to the people\nwho are going to use this thing,"},{"time":202239,"text":"for example, poor families, rural doctors,"},{"time":204866,"text":"overloaded nurses,\neven repair technicians."},{"time":208046,"text":"We thought we had all our bases\ncovered, we'd done everything right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211282,"text":"Well, it turns out there's this\nwhole constellation of people"},{"time":214172,"text":"who have to be involved\nin a product for it to be successful:"},{"time":217059,"text":"manufacturing, financing,\ndistribution, regulation."},{"time":219773,"text":"Michael Free at PATH\nsays you have to figure out"},{"time":222050,"text":"who will \"choose, use and pay the dues\""},{"time":224708,"text":"for a product like this."},{"time":226022,"text":"And I have to ask the question\nthat VCs always ask:"},{"time":228490,"text":"\"Sir, what is your business,\nand who is your customer?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":231364,"text":"Who is our customer?"},{"time":233129,"text":"Well, here's an example."},{"time":234321,"text":"This is a Bangladeshi hospital director\noutside his facility."},{"time":237616,"text":"It turns out he doesn't buy\nany of his equipment."},{"time":240477,"text":"Those decisions are made\nby the Ministry of Health"},{"time":243267,"text":"or by foreign donors,"},{"time":244615,"text":"and it just kind of shows up."},{"time":246339,"text":"Similarly, here's a multinational\nmedical-device manufacturer."},{"time":249854,"text":"It turns out they've got to fish\nwhere the fish are."},{"time":252788,"text":"So it turns out that in emerging\nmarkets -- where the fish are --"},{"time":256149,"text":"are the emerging middle class\nof these countries --"},{"time":259268,"text":"diseases of affluence:\nheart disease, infertility."},{"time":262746,"text":"So it turns out that design\nfor outcomes in one aspect"},{"time":267248,"text":"really means thinking about design\nfor manufacture and distribution."},{"time":270796,"text":"OK, that was an important lesson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273007,"text":"Second, we took that lesson and tried\nto push it into our next project."},{"time":277197,"text":"So we started by finding a manufacturer,"},{"time":279730,"text":"an organization called MTTS in Vietnam,"},{"time":282052,"text":"that manufactures newborn-care\ntechnologies for Southeast Asia."},{"time":285474,"text":"Our other partner is East Meets West,"},{"time":287382,"text":"an American foundation\nthat distributes that technology"},{"time":290032,"text":"to poor hospitals around that region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292706,"text":"So we started with them, saying,\n\"Well, what do you want?"},{"time":295413,"text":"What's a problem you want to solve?\""},{"time":297166,"text":"And they said, \"Let's work\non newborn jaundice.\""},{"time":299695,"text":"So this is another one of these\nmind-boggling global problems."},{"time":303781,"text":"Jaundice affects two-thirds\nof newborns around the world."},{"time":307544,"text":"Of those newborns, one in 10 roughly,"},{"time":312092,"text":"if it's not treated,\nthe jaundice gets so severe"},{"time":314596,"text":"that it leads to either\na life-long disability,"},{"time":317293,"text":"or the kids could even die."},{"time":320330,"text":"There's one way to treat jaundice,"},{"time":322073,"text":"and that's what's called\nan exchange transfusion."},{"time":324637,"text":"So as you can imagine, that's expensive\nand a little bit dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328505,"text":"There is another cure."},{"time":330314,"text":"It's very technological,\nit's very complex, a little daunting."},{"time":335981,"text":"You've got to shine blue light on the kid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338227,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339313,"text":"Bright blue light on as much\nof the skin as you can cover."},{"time":342788,"text":"How is this a hard problem?"},{"time":344693,"text":"I went to MIT. OK, we'll figure that out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350358,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":351818,"text":"So here's an example."},{"time":353009,"text":"This is an overhead phototherapy device\nthat's designed for American hospitals,"},{"time":357541,"text":"and here's how it's supposed to be used."},{"time":359543,"text":"It's over the baby,\nilluminating a single patient."},{"time":364166,"text":"Take it out of an American hospital,"},{"time":365929,"text":"send it overseas\nto a crowded facility in Asia,"},{"time":368162,"text":"here's how it's actually used."},{"time":369638,"text":"The effectiveness of phototherapy\nis a function of light intensity."},{"time":372885,"text":"These dark blue squares show you\nwhere it's effective phototherapy."},{"time":376316,"text":"Here's what it looks\nlike under actual use."},{"time":378371,"text":"So those kids on the edges aren't actually\nreceiving effective phototherapy."},{"time":382076,"text":"But without training,\nwithout some kind of light meter,"},{"time":385526,"text":"how would you know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":387336,"text":"We see other examples\nof problems like this."},{"time":389421,"text":"Here's a neonatal intensive care unit,"},{"time":391267,"text":"where moms come in to visit their babies."},{"time":393253,"text":"And keep in mind that Mom\nmaybe just had a C-section,"},{"time":395772,"text":"so that's already kind of a bummer."},{"time":397662,"text":"Mom's visiting her kid."},{"time":399059,"text":"She sees her baby naked,\nlying under some blue lights,"},{"time":402218,"text":"looking kind of vulnerable."},{"time":404357,"text":"It's not uncommon for Mom\nto put a blanket over the baby."},{"time":408214,"text":"From a phototherapy standpoint,\nmaybe not the best behavior."},{"time":412112,"text":"In fact, that sounds kind of dumb."},{"time":414010,"text":"Except, what we've learned is that\nthere's no such thing as a dumb user --"},{"time":418824,"text":"there are only dumb products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421510,"text":"We have to think like existentialists:"},{"time":423372,"text":"it's not the painting\nwe would have painted,"},{"time":425460,"text":"it's the painting\nthat we actually painted."},{"time":427499,"text":"It's the use -- designed for actual use."},{"time":430033,"text":"How are people actually going to use this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":432477,"text":"So, similarly, when we think\nabout our partner MTTS,"},{"time":435581,"text":"they've made some amazing technologies\nfor treating newborn illnesses."},{"time":439033,"text":"So here's an overhead warmer and a CPAP."},{"time":441366,"text":"They're inexpensive, really rugged."},{"time":444135,"text":"They've treated 50,000 kids\nin Vietnam with this technology."},{"time":446996,"text":"But here's the problem:"},{"time":448377,"text":"Every doctor in the world,\nevery hospital administrator,"},{"time":451204,"text":"has seen TV -- curse those \"ER\" reruns!"},{"time":456480,"text":"Turns out they all know what a medical\ndevice is supposed to look like."},{"time":460637,"text":"They want Buck Rogers,\nthey don't want effective."},{"time":464049,"text":"It sounds crazy, it sounds dumb,"},{"time":465831,"text":"but there are actually hospitals\nwho would rather have no equipment"},{"time":469022,"text":"than something that looks\ncheap and crummy."},{"time":471102,"text":"So again, if we want\npeople to trust a device,"},{"time":474420,"text":"it has to look trustworthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475852,"text":"So thinking about outcomes,"},{"time":477367,"text":"it turns out appearances matter."},{"time":479768,"text":"We took all that information together."},{"time":482299,"text":"We tried, this time, to get it right."},{"time":484654,"text":"And here's what we developed."},{"time":486066,"text":"This is the Firefly phototherapy device,"},{"time":488026,"text":"except this time,\nwe didn't stop at the concept car."},{"time":491687,"text":"From the very beginning, we started\nby talking to manufacturers."},{"time":494965,"text":"Our goal is to make\na state-of-the-art product"},{"time":498133,"text":"that our partner MTTS\ncan actually manufacture."},{"time":500839,"text":"Our goal is to study how they work,\nthe resources they have access to,"},{"time":504950,"text":"so that they can make this product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507505,"text":"So that's the design\nfor manufacture question."},{"time":510020,"text":"When we think about actual use,"},{"time":511879,"text":"you'll notice that Firefly\nhas a single bassinet."},{"time":514212,"text":"It only fits a single baby,"},{"time":516109,"text":"and the idea here is it's obvious\nhow you ought to use this device."},{"time":520167,"text":"If you try to put more than one kid in,"},{"time":522064,"text":"you're stacking them on top of each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524117,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525773,"text":"So the idea here is you want\nto make it hard to use wrong."},{"time":528568,"text":"In other words, you want to make\nthe right way to use it"},{"time":531259,"text":"the easiest way to use it."},{"time":533221,"text":"Another example -- again, silly Mom."},{"time":536257,"text":"Silly Mom thinks her baby looks cold,\nwants to put a blanket over the baby."},{"time":539834,"text":"That's why we have lights\nabove and below the baby in Firefly,"},{"time":542780,"text":"so if Mom does put a blanket\nover the baby,"},{"time":544841,"text":"it's still receiving effective\nphototherapy from below."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548636,"text":"Last story here:"},{"time":549978,"text":"I've got a friend in India who told me"},{"time":551897,"text":"that you haven't really tested\na piece of electronic technology"},{"time":554902,"text":"for distribution in Asia,"},{"time":556968,"text":"until you've trained a cockroach\nto climb in and pee"},{"time":559437,"text":"on every single little\ncomponent on the inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561913,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563721,"text":"You think it's funny."},{"time":565104,"text":"I had a laptop in the Peace Corps,"},{"time":567342,"text":"and the screen had all these\ndead pixels on it."},{"time":569570,"text":"And one day I looked in --\nthey were all dead ants"},{"time":572379,"text":"that had gotten\ninto my laptop and perished."},{"time":574467,"text":"Those poor ants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575642,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577206,"text":"So with Firefly, what we did is --\nthe problem is electronics get hot,"},{"time":580794,"text":"and you have to put in vents\nor fans to keep them cool --"},{"time":583540,"text":"in most products."},{"time":584808,"text":"We decided we can't put a \"Do not enter\"\nsign next to the vent."},{"time":589617,"text":"We actually got rid of all that stuff."},{"time":591640,"text":"So Firefly's totally sealed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593365,"text":"These are the kinds of lessons --"},{"time":594981,"text":"as awkward as it was\nto be a pretty goofy teenager,"},{"time":597641,"text":"much worse to be a frustrated designer."},{"time":599648,"text":"So I was thinking, \"What I really\nwant to do is change the world."},{"time":602782,"text":"I have to pay attention\nto manufacturing and distribution."},{"time":605549,"text":"I have to pay attention to how people\nare actually going to use a device."},{"time":609564,"text":"I actually have to pay attention.\nThere's no excuse for failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612604,"text":"I have to think like an existentialist."},{"time":614502,"text":"I have to accept that there\nare no dumb users, only dumb products.\""},{"time":617766,"text":"We have to ask ourselves hard questions."},{"time":620160,"text":"Are we designing\nfor the world that we want?"},{"time":623240,"text":"Are we designing\nfor the world that we have?"},{"time":625906,"text":"Are we designing\nfor the world that's coming,"},{"time":628044,"text":"whether we're ready or not?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":629362,"text":"I got into this business\ndesigning products."},{"time":632762,"text":"I've since learned that if you really want\nto make a difference in the world,"},{"time":636449,"text":"you have to design outcomes."},{"time":638236,"text":"And that's design that matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639801,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640977,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}